(1776, 49, '3 An Enhanced FOR loop in Java misses ___ and __ compared to the old-style FOR loop.', ' Speed and Easiness', ' Initialization, Increment/Decrement', ' Semicolons, Variables', ' None', 'B', 'The condition part is not required as the Enhanced FOR loop iterates through all elements of the Collection from staring to end.'),
(1777, 49, '3 A BREAK or CONTINUE statement applies only to the ___ loop.', ' Inner loop or the loop containing break or continue', ' always Outer loop', ' Sometimes inner loop, sometimes outer loop', ' None', 'A', ''),
(1778, 49, '3 A BREAK-WITH-LABEL or CONTINUE-WITH-LABEL are used in particular in Java to select __ loop either to Break or Continue.', ' Inner loop', ' Outer loop', ' -', ' -', 'B', 'Use the Labels only to choose outer loops. Otherwise, simply use BREAK or CONTINUE without any label.'),
(1779, 49, ' Choose rules for naming a Label in Java below.', ' The name of a label or identifier may start only with Alphabet, Underscore ( _ ) or Dollar ($) symb', ' A label is kept before the loop in general', ' Duplicate label names are not allowed', ' All', 'D', ''),
(1780, 49, '4 State TRUE or FALSE. You can exit an inner loop without using a BREAK statement but with a CONTINUE and Label on the outer loop.', ' FALSE', ' TRUE', ' -', ' -', 'B', ''),
(1781, 49, '4 The keyword \"goto\" can be used in Java programs with labels. (TRUE/FALSE)', ' FALSE', ' TRUE', ' -', ' -', 'A', 'The keyword \"goto\" is still a reserved keyword. It can not be used.'),
